[[File:Fighting Kraken.png|thumb|300px|A player battles the Kraken after disturbing its slumber.]]
The [[Kraken]] is a [[Boss#Slayer_bosses|Slayer boss]] and can therefore only be killed while on a [[Slayer task]] to kill ([[Cave kraken|cave]]) kraken. The Kraken is located in the [[Kraken Cove]].

It is recommended to use the [[Magic]] attack style to fight the Kraken, as it is highly resistant to [[Ranged]] and immune to [[Melee]], due to the fact that it cannot be reached by Melee attacks. As there are no complex mechanics when facing this boss, the Kraken is a popular [[boss]]. Therefore it may be hard to find an empty world. Players can alternatively create an [[instance]] for {{Coins|25,000}} coins, which lasts until the player leaves or logs out.

==Requirements==
*Level {{SCP|Slayer|87}} to deal damage against the Kraken.

===Recommendations===
*High [[combat]] stats. Although not required, see the skill levels below for an indication of the advised stats:
**If using [[Magic]]:
***Level {{SCP|Magic|75}} or higher to equip the correct staves.
*Partial completion of {{SCP|Quest}} [[Fairytale II - Cure a Queen]] for access to the [[fairy rings]] network.
*[[Bracelet of slaughter|Bracelet of Slaughter]] to extend trip length.

==Getting there==
The Kraken is located in a separated section of the [[Kraken Cove]]. The quickest way to get to this dungeon is via [[fairy rings]]:
*Use the code {{Fairycode|AKQ}}, then run west to the dungeon entrance.

Run north after entering the Kraken cove to find the entrance to the Kraken's lair.

==Mechanics==
===Releasing the Kraken===
[[File:Kraken fight.png|thumb|300px|Without a fishing explosive, players must disturb the four smaller whirlpools before they can successfully release the Kraken.]]
To disturb the Kraken and start the fight, the player must use a [[fishing explosive]] on the large whirlpool, or attack the four small whirlpools and then attack the large whirlpool.

When using explosives, the impact audio cue indicates the Kraken is active, and attacks will register even if it has not emerged visually; any attacks made before the cue will produce no response.

The smaller whirlpools will change into four [[Enormous Tentacle]]s, while the central whirlpool will change into the [[Kraken]] itself.

===Attack styles===
During the fight, the player will be attacked by four [[Enormous Tentacle]]s and by the [[Kraken]] itself:
*The Kraken only attacks with a [[typeless]] [[magical ranged]] attack:
**'Typeless' means that [[protection prayers]] will not have any effect.
**'Magical ranged' means that the attack accuracy is decided by the ranged attack bonuses of the Kraken and the magic defence bonuses of the player.
**The max hit of this attack is 28.
**The attack isn't very accurate and has an attack speed of 4 (i.e. every 2.4 seconds).
*The Enormous Tentacles only attack with a [[typeless]] [[magical ranged]] attack:
**'Typeless' means that [[protection prayers]] will not have any effect.
**'Magical ranged' means that the attack accuracy is decided by the ranged attack bonuses of the Enormous Tentacles and the magic defence bonuses of the player.
**The max hit of this attack is 2.
**The attack is very accurate and has an attack speed of 4 (i.e. every 2.4 seconds).

==Tips==
===Instance===
The Kraken is a popular [[boss]], therefore it may be hard to find an empty world. To combat this, players can create a private [[instance]] for {{Coins|25,000}} coins.

An advantage of a private instance is that dropped items stay on the ground for a longer period of time. Normally, items disappear after two minutes upon being dropped and other players can see it after one minute. However, this is not an issue if instancing, as dropped items disappear in 30 minutes within the [[Kraken Cove]] instance. As the [[Kraken]] regularly drops a generous amount of food in the form of 5 [[edible seaweed]] or 5 [[shark]]s, the instance makes it a lot easier on the player to juggle these food sources before they disappear.

It is highly recommend to turn Auto Retaliate off when fighting the Kraken, as the tentacles continue to attack the player after it has been killed, resulting in wasted runes or weapon charges should your character attack them in return.

When exiting the instance, either by leaving, dying, or logging out, all items on the ground will be permanently lost. If a player dies, all items carried will be moved to a gravestone outside the instance.

===Prayer===
As the Kraken and its tentacles use typeless attacks, the [[protection prayers]] have no effect. Players that bring an [[imbued heart]] should pray [[Preserve]]. Players with low [[Magic]] and/or [[Defence]] may consider praying [[Augury]] or [[Mystic Might]] to increase their magical defence.

